Thanks for playing MORTAR and see you soon again!

usage: mortar [options] <player names>

Options:
	-c #	configuration file name
	-l #	language used in the game messages
	-r #	how many rounds are played (1-)
	-w #	game area width (may get ignored)
	-h #	game area height (may get ignored)
	-p #	path for configuration file and data

There has to be names at least for two players.

For example:
	mortar -p data -c moon.cfg -l english -r 3 -w 640 -h 480 One Two
	mortar -p /usr/lib/games/mortar/ "mr Who" Hubba-Bubba "Just me"
